<P>
HIGH-FIVE MRS. BS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Thank you for the "Five Mrs. Buchanans," Saturday nights on CBS.It is one of 
the best comedies out there, and the characters are superb. Though Eileen 
Heckart and Judith Ivey steal the show, with their clipped, well-timed humor, 
each character really does a great job. 
</P>
<P>
 That's saying a lot for CBS, because most of the time there isn't much to 
watch on that network. We have "The Nanny," and "Dave's World," but the "Five 
Mrs. Buchanans" are by far the best and funniest on TV right now (besides 
"Frasier"). 
</P>
<P>
 Toni Jacobson, Monterey Park 
</P>
