<P>
MOVIES TO TAPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kevin Thomas 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 35 Up (Bravo Sunday at 8 p.m.) is the latest -- 1991 -- installment in Michael 
Apted's startling and unique series of five British documentaries that started 
with "Seven Up" in 1964.Every seven years Apted checks in on the lives of 14 
children from the age of 7 who represent a cross-section of society. 
</P>
<P>
 La Femme Nikita (Bravo Saturday at 6 p.m. and midnight), Luc Besson's 1990 
imitation high-tech urban thriller, follows the rules only to subvert them into 
a feminist fable. The result is shallow, sometimes silly, but Anne Parillaud, 
in the title role, is riveting as a free-lance murderer turned government 
agent. 
</P>
