<HEADLINE>
<P>
PAPERBACKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 IT'S THE THOUGHT THAT COUNTS: For Better or For Worse 15th Anniversary 
Collection by Lynn Johnston (Andrews & McMeel: $12.95; 230 pp., paperback 
original). Over the last decade and a half, "For Better or for Worse" has 
developed into an intelligent, inclusive portrait of family life in North 
America in the late 20th Century. Like Frank King ("Gasoline Alley"), Johnston 
allows her characters to age and refuses to tie every story up neatly. In a 
series of interesting notes, she comments on events in her life that influenced 
specific strips, and discusses audience reactions to the controversial series 
in which one of her teen-age characters revealed he was gay. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Book Review 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA112794-0025 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 102411 </DOCID>
