<HEADLINE>
<P>
PAPERBACKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 THE PRIMAL CHEESEBURGER: A Generous Helping of Food History Served Up on a Bun 
by Elisabeth Rozin (Penguin: $8.95; 230 pp., paperback original). Rozin argues 
that a cheeseburger with fries and a Coke is the quintessential American meal: 
One that the nation's citizens consume in staggering numbers and export 
throughout the world. She discusses each component (meat, bun, condiments, 
etc.) offering brief histories and comments, concluding that the cheeseburger 
offers a particularly appealing combination of red meat and fat: foods that 
were long restricted to the tables of the wealthy. 
</P>
