<HEADLINE>
<P>
CRITIC'S PICK: 'WAYNE'S WORLD 2' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kevin Thomas 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 This 1993 release is just as hilarious as the 1992 original, which was one of 
the most distinctive American comedies in years. Mike Myers and Dana Carvey 
(left) return as those two Aurora, Ill., youths who host a goofy late-night 
cable-access TV show.They're a couple of small-town guys who like to think of 
themselves as being incredibly hip yet possess considerable naivete. A year has 
passed since Myers' cocky Wayne and Carvey's somewhat dim Garth have resisted 
selling out their show for big bucks, and they're at loose ends when Wayne hits 
upon staging a huge concert -- "Waynestock." Along with such bands as 
Aerosmith, Pearl Jam and Van Halen, Wayne wants his gorgeous girlfriend (Tia 
Carrere) to appear, but a suave record producer (Christopher Walken) wants to 
whisk her out to the West Coast for reasons Wayne suspects are not entirely 
professional. With a hilarious turn by Kim Basinger (pictured) as Garth's date 
(HBO, Saturday at 8 p.m.). Kevin Thomas 
</P>
