<HEADLINE>
<P>
A PARODY? SURE. FUNNY? WELL . . . 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Poor dears, feeling lonely and wanted to generate a bit of mail? Certainly 
there can be no other reason to print Gene Weingarten's parody, "But Then, 
Women Can Find Their Own Socks" (Nov. 1). 
</P>
<P>
 Just don't expect all the hate mail to come from humorless women who failed to 
get the point. I got the joke, and I still hated it. You can expect some mail 
from humorless men, however, who will want to elect Mr. Weingarten President or 
possibly God. 
</P>
<P>
 DENISE WOERNER 
</P>
<P>
 Reseda 
</P>
