LOS ANGELES CITY HALL JOURNAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL KRIKORIAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 CITY COUNCIL 
</P>
<P>
 * CHRISTMAS PARADE -- Approved the closures from noon to midnight of the 
streets on the route of today's Hollywood Christmas Parade. The parade will 
begin at 6 p.m. at Sunset Boulevard and Van Ness Avenue and proceed west to 
Highland Avenue, north to Hollywood Boulevard and east to Bronson Avenue.The 
Hollywood Chamber of Commerce expects a crowd of more than 1 million to see the 
parade. 
</P>
<P>
 * HOLLYWOOD AIDS HOUSING -- Authorized the Los Angeles Housing Department to 
issue a $111,000 loan to the St. Andrew's Community Limited Partnership for the 
rehabilitation of the St. Andrew's Bungalow Court at 1514-1544 N. St. Andrew's 
Place. The building will provide affordable housing for people with AIDS or who 
are HIV-positive. Rehabilitation of the 16-unit facility will include new 
roofing, replacement of plumbing and electrical systems, and installation of 
new kitchen and bathroom fixtures. 
</P>
<P>
 * SPEED LIMITS -- Approved raising the speed limit on Sawtelle Boulevard 
between Palms Boulevard and Venice Boulwevard to 40 mph from 35 mph. Also 
approved raising the speed limit on Culver Boulevard between Nicholson Street 
and Pacific Avenue to 30 mph from 25 mph. MICHAEL KRIKORIAN 
