REAL ESTATE MANAGEMENT PANEL WILL DISCUSS FUTURE OF MARKET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A breakfast focusing on the future of the real estate market in the Los 
Angeles area will be held Dec. 7 at 7 a.m. in the Biltmore Hotel, 506 S. Grand 
Ave., by the Institute of Real Estate Management (IREM). 
</P>
<P>
 Panelists include Jack Kyser, chief economist, the Economic Development Corp.; 
Richard Pink, national director of acquisitions, TCW Realty Advisors; Donald 
Crocker, president, J. E. Robert Co. Inc., and J. Squire Junger, deputy 
worldwide director, Arthur Anderson, Real Estate Services Group. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets are $35 each in advance and $40 at the door. For reservation and other 
information, phone the IREM at (310) 358-1515. 
