<HEADLINE>
<P>
COWS REMAIN POPULAR ON AND OFF THE FARM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Special to the Times 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 These days, it seems cows are as popular in urban homes as they are on farms 
and ranches. Decorating with cow themes remains as trendy as ever. 
</P>
<P>
 Here's a do-it-yourself project that will add a little of that bovine charm to 
your home or yard. This cow planter can be used indoors or out: just fill it up 
with potted plants or flowers and put it on the porch, in the yard or in the 
kitchen or den. 
</P>
<P>
 The completed cow planter measures 37 inches long by 14 inches wide by 21 
inches high. 
</P>
<P>
 The Cow Planter plan, No. 825, is $6.50 and includes step-by-step directions 
with 15 photos, full-size traceable patterns, exploded diagrams and a shopping 
list and cutting schedule. 
</P>
