<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS, TIPS & BARGAINS: A TAXING MATTER IN BRITAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Britain-bound? Be prepared to tack on another $16 or so for a new departure 
tax at British airports.Passengers traveling within Britain and to European 
Union countries (as well as Austria, Finland and Norway) pay about $8; for all 
other destinations, including the United States, the tax is about $16. 
(Transfers don't pay, and those on round trips to and from the same airport 
within Britain pay only once.) The tax is added to air fares -- so at least you 
don't have to fork over the 10 pounds at the airport as you're leaving. 
</P>
</TEXT>
