<P>
THE MATURE TRAVELER: SPEAK LIKE A LOCAL ABROAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HANK KOVELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Combine travel with learning a foreign language. Language Study Abroad 
arranges study courses in Mexico and Europe. Prices quoted for those over 50 
include registration, accommodations, most meals and tuition.Classes are held 
five days a week for two weeks; air fare not included: 
</P>
<P>
 * Cuernavaca, Mexico: $708. A 90-minute drive from Mexico City. 
</P>
<P>
 * Ensenada, Baja California: $600. A discount is available for those who want 
to live in their RV. 
</P>
<P>
 * Vichy, France: $831. Three hours from Paris by fast train. The college has 
been teaching French to foreigners for 28 years. 
</P>
<P>
 * Siena, Italy, one hour south of Florence: $649. Classes are held in a 
17th-Century palace. 
</P>
<P>
 * Rome, at the Torre Di Babbele (Tower of Babble) school in the center of the 
city: $513. 
</P>
<P>
 Call Language Study Abroad; telephone (818) 242-5263. 
