<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHLAND HOME SALES FLATTEN OUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 October home sales in Southern California were flat, indicating a slowdown in 
real estate activity, according to TRW REDI Property Data, a real estate 
information company. Still, home sales so far this year are 17% higher than the 
same period a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
 TRW REDI reports that between January and October more than 171,000 new and 
existing homes closed escrow compared to just under 150,000 a year ago. Within 
the Southern California region all counties have posted strong gains, with 
Orange County showing a very healthy increase of 22%. 
</P>
<P>
 "The slowdown in October sales was anticipated and is due to the usual 
seasonal factors. Long-term trends in sales activity, however, show clearly 
that Southern California's housing market is experiencing a modest recovery," 
said Nima Nattagh, TRW REDI's market analyst. Southland Home Sales 
