<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMEN'S BASKETBALL; THOMPSON LEADS USC TO VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tina Thompson scored a career-high 35 points to help 23rd-ranked USC to an 
87-76 victory over Marquette on Saturday in the opening round of the Hawkeye 
Classic. 
</P>
<P>
 Thompson, expected to be the focal point of the USC offense now that player of 
the year Lisa Leslie is gone, filled that role admirably in the Trojans' 
opener. 
</P>
<P>
 The 6-foot-3 sophomore, the Pacific 10 Conference freshman of the year last 
season, made 14 of 27 shots in topping her previous best of 24 points against 
Arizona State last February. She also had 12 rebounds as USC outrebounded 
Marquette, 62-42. 
</P>
<P>
 Guard Karleen Shields scored 24 points for USC, 17 in the first half. 
Christine Kennedy led Marquette (0-2) with 22 points. 
</P>
