<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE REGIONAL SOCCER PLAYOFFS; MOORPARK'S FISHER MAKES SAVE, SINKS 
CYPRESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Goalkeeper Amy Fisher made several key saves Saturday but none bigger than the 
final one during penalty kicks that sent Moorpark to the State women's soccer 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark, the fourth-seeded team in Southern California, and top-seeded 
Cypress were tied, 1-1, after 90 minutes of regulation and 30 minutes of 
overtime. 
</P>
<P>
 The game was decided by penalty kicks and Moorpark won, 3-2, when Fisher dived 
far to the right to knock away a shot by Cypress' Christy Rowe. Fisher had 13 
saves in regulation and four in overtime. 
</P>
<P>
 Michelle Ranuschio, Summer Salvatera, and Maureen O'Hare scored on penalty 
kicks for Moorpark (10-3-4). The state tournament is Dec. 3-4 in Sacramento. 
</P>
<P>
 Christine Tyler and Tracy Van Herk scored for Cypress, which has won three 
consecutive Orange Empire Conference titles. The Chargers end the season 
16-1-2. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the second consecutive postseason loss on penalty kicks for Cypress, 
which lost in the same manner to DeAnza in the state title game last season. 
</P>
<P>
 "We all had our Lucky Charms for breakfast today," Moorpark Coach Ken Dale 
said. "It's a tough way for either team to lose." 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress dominated the first half, but Fisher had seven saves and the teams 
were tied, 0-0. Cypress' offense struggled partly because starting forwards 
Traci Osman (ankle) and Lori Van Herk (knee) were out because of injuries. 
Osman had nine goals this season. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark's offense improved in the second half but Cypress broke the scoreless 
tie when Pam Prine scored her 10th goal off an assist by Rowe in the 81st 
minute. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark rallied about two minutes later when Christy McGowan put a rebound 
past Cypress goalkeeper April O'Brien. 
</P>
</TEXT>
