<HEADLINE>
<P>
NCAA SOCCER CHAMPIONSHIPS; UCLA, CAL STATE FULLERTON FACE SECOND-ROUND GAMES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By WENDY WITHERSPOON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 UCLA will play Southern Methodist at SMU and Cal State Fullerton will play San 
Francisco at Fullerton today in the second round of the NCAA men's soccer 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 UCLA (16-4), ranked seventh, is led by Ante Razov, who has 13 goals and five 
assists for 31 points.Razov scored the winning goal with 4:24 to play in 
overtime to give UCLA a 3-2 first-round victory over unranked Alabama 
Birmingham last Sunday. The Bruins' first playoff victory since 1991 ended a 
three-game losing streak. 
</P>
<P>
 UCLA played SMU in a regular-season game last year and forward Robbie LaBelle 
scored three goals to lead the Bruins to a 4-0 victory at Dallas. 
</P>
<P>
 SMU (15-3-1), ranked eighth, is led by Stefan Soufiane, who has 17 goals and 
five assists. SMU defeated 15th-ranked Wisconsin last Sunday, 2-1. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton (13-6-2), ranked 24th, is led by Eddie Soto, who has 18 goals and 
five assists. Soto scored two goals to lead Fullerton to a 3-1 overtime victory 
over 20th-ranked San Diego in a first-round game Nov. 19. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton defeated San Francisco, 1-0, last season in the third round of the 
NCAA tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Unranked San Francisco (10-6-3) defeated third-ranked Fresno State (17-3-1) on 
penalty kicks, 4-2, in a first-round game after the teams were tied, 1-1, after 
sudden-death overtime. Today's game is scheduled for 1 p.m. WENDY WITHERSPOON 
</P>
</TEXT>
