</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COLLEGE BASKETBALL TOURNAMENT; GENEROUS MOORPARK SURVIVES LATE RALLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FERNANDO DOMINGUEZ, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After leading by double digits for a good portion of the game, the Moorpark 
College men's basketball team had to hang on for a 91-88 victory over Antelope 
Valley in the semifinals of the Ventura tournament Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark (4-1) will face Ventura in the championship game tonight at 7. 
Antelope Valley will meet Santa Barbara in the third-place game at 5. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark led by as many as 17 points in the second half but the Marauders 
(3-4) pulled to within 89-88 on two free throws by Jerome Payton with 24 
seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark point guard Jaime Jaquez scored the final two points of the game on 
free throws with 13 seconds remaining. Jaquez finished with a team-high 27 
points, including 20 in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 Marauder forward Orville Turner missed a three-point attempt at the buzzer. 
Turner led all scorers with 32 points and made seven three-point shots. He also 
had nine rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 "One of the things we have to quit doing is let people back in the game," 
Moorpark Coach Al Nordquist said. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark led Kings River by 15 points in the first half of its first-round 
game Friday but escaped with a 57-50 victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Against Antelope Valley, the Raiders held a 37-35 halftime lead behind the 
shooting of Nick Foster, who scored 13 of his 23 points in the first half. He 
also had a game-high 14 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Neither team shot well from the free-throw line. 
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley shot 68.5% (24 of 35) and Moorpark shot 58.9% (23 of 39). 
Antelope Valley also couldn't find the basket from long range, making only 
44.4% (12 of 27) of its three-point attempts. 
</P>
<P>
 Guard Troy Coutee scored 15 points for Antelope Valley. Brandon McIntire and 
Derrick Barker each had 11. 
</P>
<P>
 Paul Foster contributed 16 points and 10 rebounds for Moorpark. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura 103, Santa Barbara 72 -- The Pirates (5-0) advanced to the 
championship game with their fifth 100-point performance. 
</P>
<P>
 Shannon Taylor and Curtis Gaines each scored 15 points to pace the Pirates in 
a matchup between Western State Conference North Division rivals. 
</P>
<P>
 Lance Fay, Kenny Washington and Hakeen Ward each scored 11 points for Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 Mark Kepler led Santa Barbara with 13 points. Mark Small added 12. 
</P>
</TEXT>
