Carol Smith 
</P>
<P>
 RECORD AT SCHOOL: 7-15 04,20,05,06,04 RETURNING STARTERS YR. HGT. P Susie 
Dionne Sr. 6-0 F Shannon Noonan Sr. 6-0 C 04,19,05,06,05 TOP RETURNERS YR. HGT. 
P Tiffani Mendivil So. 6-0 C Amanda Peyrebrune Sr. 5-8 F Shannon Redfern So. 
5-9 G/F Tiffany Voss Sr. 5-9 F 04,19,05,06,05 TOP NEWCOMERS YR. HGT. P April 
Baraconi Sr. 5-7 G Michelle Chambers Fr. 5-10 F/C Kristen Morley Fr. 5-7 G 
Barbara Scheil Sr. 5-8 F Tiara Stone So. 5-7 G OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Dionne played with her back to the basket last season on offense and averaged 
6.7 points. This year, she will face the basket to take advantage of her 
outside shooting ability. Smith says Noonan, who averaged 11 points last season 
and was a second-team all-league selection, will be more aggressive and 
definitely score more. Chambers will also start. Smith said she has good 
offensive skills and will provide rebounding help. But inexperience in the 
backcourt might hurt the Eagles--sophomore Stone and freshman Morley will share 
guard duties. Peyrebrune is the team's best outside shooter. "The inside game 
will be our strength," Smith said, "if we can get the ball there." Smith said 
after a year playing in her system, the Eagles' execution should have improved. 
Despite their youth, Smith said the Eagles have a good shot at the league's 
third playoff spot. SCHEDULE 
