<HEADLINE>
<P>
PLACENTIA-YORBA LINDA SCHOOL TRUSTEES PROMOTE MCHOLLAND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DANIELLE A. FOUQUETTE, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Assistant Supt. Sharon McHolland was promoted to deputy superintendent this 
week by the Placentia-Yorba Linda Unified School District Board of Trustees. 
</P>
<P>
 The board unanimously approved McHolland's promotion in a closed-door session 
before Tuesday's board meeting. She becomes the district's first deputy 
superintendent after serving as one of three assistant superintendents. 
</P>
<P>
 Since 1987, McHolland has been in charge of the district's educational 
services division, which oversees curriculum and special projects. As deputy 
superintendent, McHolland will continue to head up that division, but with as 
yet undefined additional responsibilities. She will also serve as acting 
superintendent when Supt. James O. Fleming is out of the district. 
</P>
<P>
 Fleming requested the promotion to reflect the district's commitment to 
academics, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 "Sharon has provided outstanding leadership as assistant superintendent, which 
has been reflected in our students' outstanding academic and co-curricular 
performance," Fleming said in a statement. 
</P>
<P>
 McHolland will receive a $2,500 annual raise, effective Dec. 1, bringing her 
total salary package to $91,688. 
</P>
</TEXT>
