<HEADLINE>
<P>
6 ARRESTED AFTER 2 POLICE CHASES IN ANAHEIM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From a Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police arrested four suspected gang members on suspicion of assault with a 
deadly weapon, auto theft and possession of narcotics after a high-speed car 
chase, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The pursuit was one of two police chases in the city Saturday.It began about 4 
p.m. near Orangewood Avenue and Haster Street when an Anaheim police officer 
spotted a vehicle that had been carjacked in Livermore on Thursday, Sgt. Thomas 
Lahmon said. 
</P>
<P>
 Officers pursued the car and stopped the driver at Chapman Avenue and Haster 
Street after the car had careened into a police cruiser, Lahmon said.  
</P>
<P>
 The four juveniles ran and were quickly rounded up. Police fired one shot 
during the foot chase, but no one was injured, according to police.  
</P>
<P>
 "One round was fired but nobody was hit and nobody was hurt," Lahmon said.  
</P>
<P>
 The suspects, who were all on probation for other criminal offenses, are being 
held in Orange County Juvenile Hall, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Meanwhile, at the east end of the city, another pursuit began at about 4:30 
p.m. near Pageant Street and Bainbridge Avenue when Anaheim police officers 
spotted another car that had been reported stolen, Lahmon said. 
</P>
<P>
 "The guys chased it all over the east end of Anaheim, along the pedestrian 
trail of a river bed until the driver lost control and stopped," Lahmon said.  
</P>
<P>
 The fleeing car apparently was struck by a police cruiser and knocked off the 
trail onto the bank of the river, Lahmon said. 
</P>
<P>
 Two people were being held, he said. No names or additional details were 
available late Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
