<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOOTBALL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RICK RAMIREZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Crenshaw 33, San Pedro 6--Crenshaw running backs Brandon Seals and Farrel 
Payton combined for 252 yards and five touchdowns as the Cougars won a City 4-A 
quarterfinal game at Fremont High. 
</P>
<P>
 Seals scored on runs of 14, 15 and 11 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 San Pedro's only score came on a five-yard touchdown pass from Mike Lennos to 
Mark Pappas in the closing minutes of the fourth quarter. RICK RAMIREZ 
</P>
