<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: MOORPARK; WORKERS OK CONTRACT WITH MURANAKA FARMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Field laborers and packinghouse workers at Muranaka Farms in Moorpark 
unanimously approved a new United Farm Workers contract negotiated with the 
company, officials said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 The agreement, approved at a UFW meeting Friday night, will set up an 
unprecedented labor contract in which farm workers will share in some 
management decisions, said Mario Brito, the regional director of the union. 
</P>
<P>
 "The workers had really pushed for this contract," Brito said. "This is a way 
to show that workers are really interested in keeping the company profitable." 
</P>
<P>
 The approximately 150 workers at the company, who earn from $12,000 to $14,000 
a year, will also receive 5% to 8% pay raises, union officials said. SCOTT 
