<HEADLINE>
<P>
DEANE DANA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 We read with great interest your article regarding the retirement of 
Supervisor Deane Dana (Nov. 15). 
</P>
<P>
 Among the numerous accomplishments during Supervisor Dana's distinguished 
career were the protection and preservation of Los Angeles County's Ocean 
Lifeguards. 
</P>
<P>
 Through the leadership and vision of Supervisor Dana and his chief deputy, Don 
Knabe, the world's premier ocean lifeguard service was merged into the Los 
Angeles County Fire Department. 
</P>
<P>
 This merger came at a time when the citizens of the county were in danger of 
losing their lifeguards due to financial and political strains. 
</P>
<P>
 Each year 60 million people visit the Los Angeles County beaches and Los 
Angeles County lifeguards save over 10,000 lives in ocean rescues. Thanks to 
Supervisor Dana, the people of Los Angeles County can continue to enjoy their 
precious beaches secure in the knowledge that the Los Angeles County lifeguards 
will be there to make sure that all who come out to the beach enjoy their day 
and go home safe and alive. 
</P>
<P>
 DAN ATKINS, President 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles County Lifeguard Assn. 
</P>
