COMMUNITY NEWS: MID-CITY: WESTLAKE; VARIETY OF CLASSES OPEN TO ENROLLMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Enrollment is open at Belmont Community Adult School for classes in English as 
a Second Language, computer training, U.S. citizenship and to obtain either 
high school diplomas or equivalency degree certificates. 
</P>
<P>
 Most of the classes are free, with minimal fees charged for materials. Classes 
are offered weekdays and Saturdays at the campus, 1575 W. Second St. 
</P>
<P>
 Weekday classes are also offered at these satellite campuses: Menlo Adult 
Learning Center, 1216 Menlo Ave.; Mid-City Adult Learning Center, 1510 Cambria 
St.; Virgil Adult Learning Center, 152 N. Vermont Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 250-9133. 
