control. 
</P>
<P>
 The presidential palace, which the opposition had claimed to seize earlier 
Saturday, was swarming with government officials and heavily armed supporters 
of President Dzhokhar Dudayev. 
</P>
<P>
 The government said the opposition fighters were mostly Russians and that 300 
of the 350 opposition soldiers killed were Russian. 
</P>
<P>
