declared independence in 1991. Dudayev loyalists say Moscow wants to oust the 
former Soviet air force general so Chechnya will return to the Kremlin's fold. 
</P>
<P>
 Moscow, which backs the opposition politically and reportedly gives financial 
support, has denied providing any military help. 
</P>
