</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL 1994-1995: SEA VIEW LEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 WOODBRIDGE 03,17,09,08 1993-94 RECORDS OVERALL LEAGUE 32-1 14-0 COACH: Eric 
Bangs 
</P>
<P>
 RECORD AT SCHOOL: 263-68 04,20,05,06,04 RETURNING STARTERS YR. HGT. P Angela 
Burgess Sr. 6-4 C Melanie Pearson Jr. 6-1 F Erin Stovall So. 5-7 G Tami Weaver 
Jr. 5-5 G 04,19,05,06,04 TOP RETURNERS YR. HGT. P Erin Conley Jr. 6-1 C Carly 
Moss So. 5-7 G Del Sperduti Sr. 5-6 G Fernanda Villalba Sr. 5-6 F Lisa Weaver 
Sr. 5-11 F 04,19,05,06,04 TOP NEWCOMERS YR. HGT. P Josie Christensen Sr. 5-11 F 
Krissy DuPerron So. 5-10 F Nicole Roberts Fr. 5-7 G OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 The Warriors did not lose last season until they reached the State Division II 
final. Duplicating that feat depends on whether the four returning starters can 
fill the leadership void left by graduated guard Jamie Oenning, who led the 
team with an average of 13.5 points. But Burgess averaged 13.3 points and 12.4 
rebounds, Pearson averaged 11 points and eight rebounds, and Bangs' lineup will 
be deeper with the addition of two transfers, DuPerron and Christensen. "Both 
of them are real steady players," Bangs said. "Being able to go seven, eight, 
nine deep makes a difference. We were about six-deep last year." Weaver, who 
had a solid performance in the playoffs last season, tore her anterior cruciate 
ligament the week of the State final and is not at full strength yet. Bangs 
said his team is motivated by last season's only loss, but it has worked very 
hard and likely could be better this season. SCHEDULE 
</P>
<P>
 December 1 vs. Edison; 3-9 Woodbridge tournament; 19-23 at Santa Barbara 
tournament; 26-29 at Costa Mesa tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 January 3 at Esperanza; 6 at Santa Margarita; 10 at Corona del Mar; 12 at 
Irvine; 14 at Villa Park; 17 vs. El Toro; 19 at Newport Harbor; 27 vs. Santa 
Margarita; 31 vs. Corona del Mar. 
</P>
<P>
 February 2 vs. Irvine; 4 vs. Long Beach Poly; 7 at El Toro; 9 vs. Newport 
Harbor. 
</P>
</TEXT>
